This means that the moving average filter can be computed quite cheaply on =
real time data with a FIFO / <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circu=
lar_buffer" title=3D"Circular buffer">circular buffer</a> and only 3 arithm=
etic steps.
</p><p>During the initial filling of the FIFO / circular buffer the samplin=
g window is equal to the data-set size thus <span class=3D"mwe-math-element=
 mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-ma=
thml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/M=
