<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Cumulative_average">Cumulat=
ive average</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3D=
Moving_average&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: Cu=
mulative average"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">]</span></span></div>
<p>In a <b>cumulative average</b> (<b>CA</b>), the data arrive in an ordere=
d datum stream, and the user would like to get the average of all of the da=
ta up until the current datum. For example, an investor may want the averag=
e price of all of the stock transactions for a particular stock up until th=
e current time. As each new transaction occurs, the average price at the ti=
me of the transaction can be calculated for all of the transactions up to t=
hat point using the cumulative average, typically an equally weighted <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Average" title=3D"Average">average</a> =
of the sequence of <i>n</i> values <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math=
-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y=
" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathM=
L" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle x_{1}.\ldots ,x_{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>.</mo>
        <mo>=E2=80=A6<!-- =E2=80=A6 --></mo>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle x_{1}.\ldots =
,x_{n}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/d0f5d7d42eb3825e0c04f90d638c4f26acd2dd67" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:10.11ex; height:2.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle x_{=
1}.\ldots ,x_{n}}"></span> up to the current time:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle {\textit {CA}}_{n}=3D{{x_{1}+\cdots +x_{n}} \over n}\,.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mtext class=3D"MJX-tex-mathit" mathvariant=3D"italic">CA</mt=
ext>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <msub>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mo>=E2=8B=AF<!-- =E2=8B=AF --></mo>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <msub>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi>n</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
            </mrow>
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\textit {CA}=
}_{n}=3D{{x_{1}+\cdots +x_{n}} \over n}\,.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/91507f689b79243c79028d86b4af0dc0f8776b66" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -1.838ex; width:22.914ex; height:5.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {=
\textit {CA}}_{n}=3D{{x_{1}+\cdots +x_{n}} \over n}\,.}"></span>
</p><p>The brute-force method to calculate this would be to store all of th=
e data and calculate the sum and divide by the number of points every time =
a new datum arrived. However, it is possible to simply update cumulative av=
erage as a new value, <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inli=
ne"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"di=
splay: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D=
"{\displaystyle x_{n+1}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle x_{n+1}}</ann=
otation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/6e76103271a353337f6b3c697209cb19359807df" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:4.649ex; height:2.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle x_{=
n+1}}"></span> becomes available, using the formula
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle {\textit {CA}}_{n+1}=3D{{x_{n+1}+n\cdot {\textit {CA}}_{n}} \ov=
er {n+1}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mtext class=3D"MJX-tex-mathit" mathvariant=3D"italic">CA</mt=
ext>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <msub>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi>n</mi>
                  <mo>+</mo>
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>n</mi>
              <mo>=E2=8B=85<!-- =E2=8B=85 --></mo>
              <msub>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mtext class=3D"MJX-tex-mathit" mathvariant=3D"italic">=
CA</mtext>
                  </mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi>n</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
            </mrow>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mi>n</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\textit {CA}=
}_{n+1}=3D{{x_{n+1}+n\cdot {\textit {CA}}_{n}} \over {n+1}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/0c9c0947a999bec96f1d85f05ea66359ea7f9863" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.005ex; width:26.464ex; height:5.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {=
\textit {CA}}_{n+1}=3D{{x_{n+1}+n\cdot {\textit {CA}}_{n}} \over {n+1}}.}">=
</span>
</p><p>Thus the current cumulative average for a new datum is equal to the =
previous cumulative average, times <i>n</i>, plus the latest datum, all div=
ided by the number of points received so far, <i>n</i>+1. When all of the d=
ata arrive (<span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i> =3D <i>N</i></span>), then the=
 cumulative average will equal the final average. It is also possible to st=
ore a running total of the data as well as the number of points and dividin=
g the total by the number of points to get the CA each time a new datum arr=
ives.
</p><p>The derivation of the cumulative average formula is straightforward.=
 Using
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle x_{1}+\cdots +x_{n}=3Dn\cdot {\textit {CA}}_{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mo>=E2=8B=AF<!-- =E2=8B=AF --></mo>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mo>=E2=8B=85<!-- =E2=8B=85 --></mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mtext class=3D"MJX-tex-mathit" mathvariant=3D"italic">CA</mt=
ext>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle x_{1}+\cdots =
+x_{n}=3Dn\cdot {\textit {CA}}_{n}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/7ae385bc53e8b8499e6f021daab25b4cb8ad4174" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.671ex; width:24.118ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle x=
_{1}+\cdots +x_{n}=3Dn\cdot {\textit {CA}}_{n}}"></span>
and similarly for <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i> + 1</span>, it is seen t=
hat
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle x_{n+1}=3D(x_{1}+\cdots +x_{n+1})-(x_{1}+\cdots +x_{n})}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mo>=E2=8B=AF<!-- =E2=8B=AF --></mo>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>1</mn>
